  <PawnDiaryRimpsyche.Settings.DataSent.Body>Only nonblank segments are included:\npsyche=&lt;up to {0} localized descriptors above the configured magnitude threshold&gt;; interests=&lt;up to {1} strongest positive localized interest labels&gt;\nbase outlook: &lt;localized deterministic outlook from the dominant Rimpsyche node-family plan&gt;\nNot sent: pawn name, raw node values, raw interest scores, diary entries, memories, current Pawn Diary psychotype, or writing-style prose.</PawnDiaryRimpsyche.Settings.DataSent.Body>
  <PawnDiaryRimpsyche.Settings.TransformPromptDefault>Convert the supplied Rimpsyche-derived personality data into a complete replacement for the pawn's Pawn Diary psychotype, using one or two concise present-tense sentences. The “base outlook:” text was authored from this pawn's Rimpsyche personality; it is authoritative and is not the pawn's existing Pawn Diary psychotype. Preserve every distinct tendency, contrast, value, fear, and judgment in it. Copy or lightly combine its wording instead of replacing or generalizing it. Use the psyche descriptors and interests only as secondary emphasis when they clearly support the base outlook; never let them contradict it or create unsupported motives. Do not blend with, continue, or preserve any earlier Pawn Diary psychotype: it is absent from the input and this result replaces it. Begin with “This pawn”. Avoid vague personality adjectives and generic summaries. Do not mention Rimpsyche, scores, nodes, labels, game mechanics, instructions, or the transformation. Return the psychotype only.</PawnDiaryRimpsyche.Settings.TransformPromptDefault>
  <PawnDiaryRimpsyche.Settings.ChargedConversations>Record charged conversations</PawnDiaryRimpsyche.Settings.ChargedConversations>
  <PawnDiaryRimpsyche.Settings.ChargedConversationsDesc>Record only Rimpsyche conversations whose signed alignment clears the XML threshold. Each pawn pair has a saved cooldown; ordinary conversations remain ambient social texture.</PawnDiaryRimpsyche.Settings.ChargedConversationsDesc>

